    "question_id" : 79680495,
    "title" : "Java LocalDateTime Serialized output is giving incorrect values",
    "body" : "<p>I am working on replacing <a href=\"https://github.com/crnk-project/crnk-framework\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">crnk</a> with <a href=\"https://toedter.github.io/spring-hateoas-jsonapi/release/reference/\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">Spring Hateos Json APi</a> . I was getting a exception for LocalDateTime so I have used</p>\n<pre><code>@JsonSerialize(using = LocalDateTimeSerializer.class)\n   @JsonDeserialize(using = LocalDateTimeDeserializer.class)\n   private LocalDateTime getCreatedDate();\n</code></pre>\n<p>When I compare the output with the CRNK output I see some differences ie in CRNK I get</p>\n<pre><code>&quot;createdDate&quot;: [\n        2025,\n        6,\n        26,\n        3,\n        20,\n        27,\n       529000000\n      ]\n</code></pre>\n<p>and with Json Seraliser and Hateos I get</p>\n<pre><code>&quot;createdDate&quot;: [\n    2025,\n    6,\n    26,\n    8,\n    50,\n    27,\n   529000000\n  ]\n</code></pre>\n<p>I want to get the same output as I got for CRNK. Can some one tell me how to fix this.</p>\n",
