    "question_id" : 79680495,
    "body" : "<p>There's no concept of a timezone in a <code>LocalDateTime</code>, which is apparent from the word <code>Local</code>. The <a href=\"https://github.com/FasterXML/jackson-modules-java8/blob/2.x/datetime/src/main/java/com/fasterxml/jackson/datatype/jsr310/ser/LocalDateTimeSerializer.java\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">LocalDateTimeSerializer</a> simply writes out the individual components of <code>LocalDateTime</code> in an array, and the <a href=\"https://github.com/FasterXML/jackson-modules-java8/blob/2.x/datetime/src/main/java/com/fasterxml/jackson/datatype/jsr310/deser/LocalDateTimeDeserializer.java#L189C30-L189C78\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">LocalDateTimeDeserializer</a> reads those back. That's all that can be said based on the information in your question.</p>\n",
